	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.21]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Aridar, Falamil is actually incorrect in saying that a wind instrument has no effect on mez, but only to a point. What the wind bonus does on our mez songs is to increase the MR debuff portion of the song, thus making it easier to &gt;keep&lt; a mob mezzed.<br><br>However, by the time you are likely to receive this particular item you will almost certainly be using Dreams of Ayonae or a higher mez song. All of our mez songs after SoT (the dreams basically) do not have this MR debuff component and so the statement is also correct if taken from this standpoint.<br><br>I say that last sentence with one caveat. The Dream songs are all fairly new and as such there has been very little true testing done with them. As such it is not impossible that VI have altered the way they work to make a wind instrument more useful for these. This is unlikely, but I feel it necessary to mention so as not to provide false information.<br><br>That said, this mace seems nice to throw in the offhand at those times you are mainhanding the epic to get a proc, as long as you don't have one of the many weapons around that are better. I doubt it will see a great deal of use at other times.<br><br>(-:&nbsp;&nbsp; Zel   :-)<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
